						<p><hi rend="bold">No king (Kulōttuṅga I). Year 43: A.D. 1113.</hi></p>						

						<p>Incomplete. Three <hi rend="italic">śiva-brāhmaṇas</hi> of the temple received one <hi rend="italic">aṉṟāḍunaṟ-kācu</hi> from Jayanāgan, a native of Kundavaich-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Muḻaiyur-nāḍu, a subdivision of Geyamāṇikka-vaḷanāḍu and agreed to maintain one perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirumāgāḷamuḍaiyār at Ambar.</p>						

